rComments: Not sure if he's prepared to class, he mostly uses the examples from the textbook (But that also save your time in reading textbook! ). A nice and friendly guy, but not so good at making jokes. Easy problem set every week, midterm is easy, final is a little tricky.

He is an okay teacher, sometimes unclear but is ready to clarify any questions asked by the students. I would take his class again. Lectures were textbook based. He also cleans the board nicely which is great since profs usually miss a spot when erasing lol
average, easy midterm, little bit strict in marking, sometimes not clear in certain concepts, but all of stuffs are on the textbook.
